Example: The \'He\' Problem

**SCENARIO:** Statute says: \"He who throws water shall be liable\"

**CIVIL LAW APPROACH:**

-   Statute says \'he\' → Use teleological interpretation

-   Obviously includes \'she\'

-   Apply broadly to all persons

**COMMON LAW APPROACH (Traditional):**

-   Statute says \'he\' → Interpret literally

-   Only applies to males?

-   **NEED INTERPRETATION ACT** (Legislation defines \'he\' includes
    \'she\')

Why the Difference?

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| **ASPECT**                        | **EXPLANATION**                   |
+===================================+===================================+
| **CIVIL LAW**                     | Code = only source of law         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | If unclear → judge MUST interpret |
|                                   | freely                            |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | No other source to fall back on   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | *Risk: injustice if too narrow*   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| **COMMON LAW**                    | Statutes + Common Law exist side  |
|                                   | by side                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | If unclear → common law can fill  |
|                                   | gap                               |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Less pressure to interpret        |
|                                   | broadly                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | *Tradition of literal             |
|                                   | construction*                     |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+

England\'s Solution: The Interpretation Act

England created **legislation on how to interpret legislation!**

**INTERPRETATION ACT PROVIDES:**

-   \'He\' includes \'she\'

-   Singular includes plural

-   Other standardized interpretation rules

**WHY THIS EXISTS:**

-   English tradition = literal interpretation

-   Creates problems with gendered/number language

-   Parliament fixes it legislatively

-   Maintains grammatical approach while ensuring fairness

